# Project Meta
- Unity 6.0.3f1, URP, NGO, New Input System.
- UI stack: UI Toolkit first, with data binding preferred whenever practical.
- Development model: data-driven first (prefer config assets/ScriptableObjects over hardcoded gameplay values).
- C# 12; async uses `Awaitable`.
- `<ProjectName>.Documents/` (GDD/NDD) is the design source of truth.

## Organization
- Assets split by `Systems/` (reusable), `Features/` (project), `Core/` (shared glue).
- Enforce boundaries with per-system `.asmdef`.
- Use `--- SECTION ---` hierarchy separators in scenes.

## Code Commenting
- For new or updated editor tooling classes/windows, keep concise XML summaries on non-trivial helper methods and add brief intent comments for non-obvious constants/mappings (for example color palettes).

## Color Literal Formatting
- For hardcoded custom colors in C# (especially editor tooling), prefer `new Color32(0xRR, 0xGG, 0xBB, 0xAA)` and include a nearby `#RRGGBB`/`#RRGGBBAA` comment.
- Named engine constants (for example `Color.white`) are fine as-is.
